window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Author of the BBC Radio 2 Book Club best seller <i>Better Off Dead</i> </p> <p>From best-selling author Tom Wood comes a unique and gasp-inducing Victor thriller that turns all your expectations on their head.... </p> <p>Former CIA agent Antonio Alvarez has been tracking a dangerous murderer for years, a nameless hitman responsible for numerous homicides. Once, the Agency deflected him away from his search, but now a promotion has given him a second chance to right the past. </p> <p>Only problem is the murderer has vanished. </p> <p>Thousands of miles away, the assassin known as Victor has stopped working - recently he began to care; he made mistakes. But there's another assassin, Raven, who needs his help - and she is hard to refuse.... </p> <p>Enter a world of betrayal, tension and twists perfect for fans of Gregg Hurwitz (<i>Orphan X</i>, <i>The Nowhere Man</i>), James Swallow (<i>Nomad</i>, <i>Exile</i>) and Terry Hayes (<i>I Am Pilgrim</i>, <i>Day of the Locust</i>). </p>"; 
